  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protecting and Supporting Human Rights Defenders in LAC- Regional coordination</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project provides additional funds to the regional coordination of a project that aims to support and protect human right defenders at risk working on land and environmental rights in Latin America, with a focus on Colombia and Guatemala.  In recent years, we have seen a significant increase in the number of human rights defenders killed, threatened, stigmatised and criminalised across Latin America. This project will provide urgent protection and capacity strengthening of human rights defenders at risk working in remote rural areas and will enable their cases to be heard at national and international level through advocacy and communications work. It has a particular focus on the most marginalised and excluded groups, namely indigenous and afro-descendent communities.</narrative>
  </description>
